notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56O.
issue_place_s: Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States of America
issue_obverse_legend_s: FIVE POUNDS. THIS BILL shall pass current for FIVE POUNDS within the PROVINCE of Pennsylvania, according to an Act of Assembly, made in the 32d Year of the Reign of King GEORGE II. Dated the 25th day of April, 1759. Five Pounds.
issue_reverse_legend_s: ONE HUNDRED SHILLINGS. | To Counterfeit is DEATH. | Printed by B. FRANKLIN, and D. HALL. 1759. | FIVE POUNDS
